      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DEEP STEALTH (6) returned from a five-month spell with an eye-catching effort over this distance at Port Macquarie a fortnight ago, charging home late through the heavy conditions to be beaten narrowly in a Class 1. This looks a shade easier so with that run under the belt she looks a great chance to go one better. EVIL LOVER (12) finally won her maiden when resuming two back at Armidale. Worked home well to finish fourth at her latest appearance over 1205m at Coffs Harbour in heavy ground. Placed six times at this trip and with the light weight is a genuine contender. LORD SEYMOUR (4) disappointed at Inverell recently after a first-up maiden win at Coffs Harbour. Worth another chance with more give in the ground today. PRESTIGE PAK (1) returned in good order at Ballina seven weeks ago and hasn't been seen since. Query on a heavy deck but cannot be ruled out. BACK ON DE QUO (2) was a little below par first-up at Ballina but deserves another chance.",
